ory has no basis: she did not own a dog. It appears to have attached to her name because she was the only first-class woman whose whereabouts during the disaster were entirely unknown.","number":2}],"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Ann Elizabeth Isham","first_name":"Ann","middle_name":"Eliza","maiden_name":"Isham","married_names":[],"nickname":"Lizzy","photo_url":"https://www.wikitree.com/photo.php/7/70/Isham-836.png"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"ann-isham-1862"},"HD1151":{"id":"HD1151","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"HD1149","mother_id":"X00349"},"tags":["military","lawyer","west_point"],"sources":[{"short":"Wikipedia — Edward Swift Isham"}],"birth":{"year":1865,"month":8,"day":16,"city":"Heidelberg","country":"Germany"},"death":{"year":1906,"month":5,"day":19,"city":"Surry","county":"Cheshire County","state":"New Hampshire"},"gender":"male","marriages":[],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"header":"Born in Heidelberg while his father toured Europe","body":"Pierrepont Isham Jr. was born in Heidelberg, Germany on August 16, 1865, while his father Edward Swift Isham was on a two-year European tour after his term in the Illinois House of Representatives. He graduated from West Point in 1887 and served briefly in the 7th Cavalry Regiment — the regiment Custer had commanded at Little Bighorn just eleven years earlier. He then studied law with his father and became a partner at Isham Lincoln & Beale.","number":1}],"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Pierpont Isham","first_name":"Pierpont","l